column21: I prefer teleopration since it requires less physical demanding compare to the kinesthetic teaching
I failed once, the main reason is that I am nearsighted and my head is larger than most of people, it is hard for me to wear the my glass when using the vr equipment.

I did not feel any discomfort to during this project. This project is so interesting! I found teleoperation makes it easy to adjust the angle that the arm grasps the cube. And the cube seems distorted when viewed by helmet. The ring on the arm is important for me to adjust the trajectory of the movement, and I will pay more attention to it during teleoperation.

Need a clear understanding of the target point (the red circle and the dot), actions become easier after knowing how it works. It seems easier for performing task through KT including both low level and medium level tasks, as it doesn’t require extra thinking for the joint mobility for the robot. The headset was not very comfortable after wearing for a certain amount of time, it also doesn’t as clear as I expected. Would strongly recommend for one more round of task, I feel like I just started to understand the working principles for the robot and the tasks finished.
Need to grasp centre of mass for better grasp in teleoperation
Sometimes cannot grasp the block, Feel a bit dizzy

Aid:  If there is a level function which can help me to control, and a force function help me to know my controlling  is correct or not.  Voice reminder. Grid  Visualise the trajectoty, explore new or optimal path   Visualisation makes me afraid of movements  Whiteboard not fixed  Optimal path   VR headset too heavy, eyes tired  Teleoperation gives you more sense of control KT just for feeling the force and control
KT more natural  Headset hot heavy  Task 2 precision

1. Wearing VR glasses sometimes could make my view sight blurry a little bit, additionally, wearing it and seeing the reality from a VR could also distracted my estimation of distance, which may affect my performance during both approaches. 2. I didn’t aware about the visualisations during the whole experiment, but I think it’s better to have some signal to note the gripper is grabbed the item, so that I know I’m ready to move the arm.  3. KT is a it hard for me to rotate ( desk too large), difficult to control (move and rotate) the arm, compared to teleoperation. Also, when doing KT, I have to move around the table, but when doing teleoperation, I can just stand in one spot and there is no many movements.
Ar affect my feeling of space Need movement assistance to stables movement from software side Quest3 is quite heavy,  Prefer teleoperation, why we need KT for robot operations

Meta quest 3’s distortion has made the hands on part a bit harder, as you would want to aim a bit in part 3. If your face is too close to the object, the distortion would be pretty bad and make it very hard to aim.  It is fairly hard for a person to keep their hand copletely stable. The slight, uncontrollable movement of the hand makes it harder for one to keep the robot completely stable, during the study, I have to use my other hand to stabilise my hand, gripping the controller.  My preference between the two ways differ and different tasks. In the first two tasks, easier to use KT as there isnt a lot of aiming that is required to complete the task. However, in the third task it is easier to use the remote controller as I can aim at a slightly further distance, makes the  not so bad and the whole task a lot easier.  Because I’ve done a lot of meta quest three gaming at home, the weight feels less obvious to me as I pay less attention to the weight of the headset.
Arrow for rings  Headset heavy, not very clear, affect feel of the word  Prefer teleoperation, better without headset, showing status on the screen
